hold command

    (A)  FUNCTION
         Hold command fixes the value of specified facility.

    (B)  SYNOPSIS

         hold  <facility>

    (C)  PARAMETERS
        <facility>
         specifies the name of facility to be inhibit to update.

    (D)  NOTES
         Facilities applied with this command can be updated with
         set, memset and memclr commands.

         Both of the data- and instruct terminals must be assigned
         value with set command before applying this command to them.

    (E)  SEE ALSO
         set command
         release command



